><p>1.05</p></td><td><p>1.48</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>69.84</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>66.53</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>64.11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>91.25</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="5"><p>* the geographical boundaries used to report lending in this table differ slightly from the NUTS1 definition.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-01-11T15:54:24.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818704/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818704/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818704/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-08","British Business Bank: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how much loan funding was provided by the British Business Bank by NUTS 1 region in each year since 2013-14.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","121468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818705","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-11","<p>As at January 2018, the British Business Bank has 229 FTE employees in the Yorkshire and Humber, and London NUTS1 regions – 80 in Yorkshire and Humber; and 149 in London. This includes figures for SULCo, who merged with the Business Bank on 1st April 2017.</p><p> </p><p>As noted in the Industrial Strategy White Paper, British Business Bank are rolling out a network of regional managers by autumn 2018 to ensure businesses across the UK know how to access sources of investment. The network will cover England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland, with managers responding to a region’s particular needs and acting as convenors to improve collaboration, sharing of expertise and the creation of networks of private and public partners.</p><p> </p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-01-11T15:48:37.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818705/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818705/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818705/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-08","British Business Bank: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many full time equivelent staff are employed by the British Business Bank in each NUTS 1 region.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","121469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818706","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-11","<p>Half of the Transforming Cities Fund will be allocated to the six mayoral combined authorities on a per capita basis. These are:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Combined Authority</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Amount </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Greater Manchester</p></td><td><p>£243m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cambridgeshire and Peterborough</p></td><td><p>£74m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>West Midlands</p></td><td><p>£250m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tees Valley</p></td><td><p>£59m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>West of England</p></td><td><p>£80m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Liverpool City Region</p></td><td><p>£134m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£840m</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p><p>The remainder of the fund will be allocated to other major cities in England via a competitive process. Further details of this process will be announced shortly.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-01-11T14:53:48.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818706/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818706/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818706/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-08","Transforming Cities Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much money from the Transforming Cities Fund his Department plans to allocate to each NUTS 1 region.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","121470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818707","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-11","<p>Following the announcement of this fund at Autumn Budget, the Government is engaging with the private sector to ensure that it is set up in the most effective way. Further details will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-01-11T14:09:25.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818707/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818707/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818707/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-08","Electric Vehicles: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much money from the Charging Infrastructure Investment Fund his Department plans to allocate to each NUTS 1 region.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","121471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818708","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-11","<p>We expect the Council’s membership to be multidisciplinary and include leading business men and women, investors, economists and academics from across the country. Our aim is for it to start work in spring 2018 and envisage that it will meet four times a year in a convenient location for all members.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-01-11T14:17:25.05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818708/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818708/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/818708/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-08","Independent Industrial Strategy Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, where the independent Industrial Strategy Council will be based when it is created in 2018.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","121472"
