"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/816744","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-01-10","<p>The Secretary of State and I have regular discussions with ministerial colleagues on a range of agricultural issues.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-01-10T16:30:21.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/816744/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/816744/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/816744/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-01-05","Agriculture: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what discussions he has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer with regard to the recommendations made on taxation by the Tenancy Reform Industry Group in October 2017.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","121171"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/816745","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-15","<p>The Chancellor keeps the tax system under review and welcomes representations from all stakeholders, including those made by the Tenancy Reform Industry Group. The Treasury will consider the recommendations made by the Tenancy Reform Industry Group and other representations in due course, including in discussions with the Tenant Farmers Association.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride","121173","2018-01-15T15:50:12.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/816745/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/816745/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/816745/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-05","Agriculture: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has assessed the recommendations on taxation made by the Tenancy Reform Industry Group in October 2017.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","121172"
